thing in San Fransico, or do they, or not?

00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:09.410
&gt;&gt; I'm surprisingly oblivious to it.

00:14:09.410 --> 00:14:10.410
&gt;&gt;

00:14:09.410 --> 00:14:10.086
[LAUGH]

00:14:10.086 --> 00:14:14.301
&gt;&gt; Like, because I think I've grown up being used to not having to think

00:14:14.301 --> 00:14:18.630
about whether I was the only person to look the way I look in a

00:14:18.630 --> 00:14:23.265
room. I tend to do the same thing here, I'll walk in somewhere and think

00:14:23.265 --> 00:14:27.510
to myself, oh why are they looking at me? I must have something in my hair.

00:14:27.510 --> 00:14:28.510
&gt;&gt;

00:14:27.510 --> 00:14:28.210
[LAUGH]

00:14:28.210 --> 00:14:30.880
&gt;&gt; Something in my teeth, that I should brushed my teeth well at the house.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:31.470
&gt;&gt; Right.

00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:33.130
&gt;&gt; I don't think to myself, oh my godness, I'm

00:14:33.130 --> 00:14:35.690
the only person in here that has darker skin pigmentation.

00:14:35.690 --> 00:14:36.110
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:14:36.110 --> 00:14:41.300
&gt;&gt; And so it takes me awhile, and so I can't I don't know. I have no idea.

00:14:41.300 --> 00:14:41.630
&gt;&gt; Yeah

00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:42.840
&gt;&gt; Someone else would have to watch.

00:14:42.840 --> 00:14:44.530
&gt;&gt; Do you think of skin pigmentation or

00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:48.060
skin color as a positive or a negative trait?

00:14:48.060 --> 00:14:53.160
&gt;&gt; I don't think of skin pigmentation as a negative or a positive thing,

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:56.510
it does have its advantages in some situations. So,

00:14:56.510 --> 00:14:59.020
if you have darker skin pigmentation you've got into

00:14:59.020 --> 00:15:01.880
the sun a lot more then someone who doesn't

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:04.810
then you're less likely to get cancer, skin cancer.

00:15:04.810 --> 00:15:07.950
&gt;&gt; Do you think of skin color, skin pigmentation

00:15:07.950 --> 00:15:10.470
is a positive or a negative trait in anyway?

00:15:13.750 --> 00:15:18.380
&gt;&gt; I think skin color can have positives, I

00:15:18.380 --> 00:15:20.610
don't think of it as negative or positive, specifically.

00:15:20.610 --> 00:15:20.840
&gt;&gt; Mm hm, sure.

00:15:20.840 --> 00:15:25.480
&gt;&gt; But I do know that, when I go out in the sun, I have the advantage of

00:15:25.480 --> 00:15:30.880
not burning or, I know that I'm less likely

00:15:30.880 --> 00:15:34.100
to get skin cancer than someone with lighter skin pigmentation.

00:15:34.100 --> 00:15:34.290
&gt;&gt; Mm hm.

00:15:34.290 --> 00:15:39.110
&gt;&gt; But on the other side, I do know that, it, you do need the sun

00:15:39.110 --> 00:15:41.780
in order for your body to produce vitamin D.

00:15:41.780 --> 00:15:42.345
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:15:42.345 --> 00:15:45.360
&gt;&gt; And in that case, if you have

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:50.190
a higher skin, if you have darker skin pigmentation.

00:15:50.190 --> 00:15:50.220
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:15:50.220 --> 00:15:52.800
&gt;&gt; Then, you're less, you're more likely to

00:15:52.800 --> 00:15:56.100
not have the ability to produce enough vitamin D.

00:15:56.100 --> 00:15:57.440
&gt;&gt; Right, exactly, and I know that there

00:15:57.440 --> 00:15:58.840
are some people who actually have to take

00:15:58.840 --> 00:16:01.780
vitamin D supplements, or they have to actually

00:16:01.780 --> 00:16:03.468
be told to go out into the sun more.

00:16:03.468 --> 00:16:03.867
&gt;&gt; Mm hmm.

00:16:03.867 --> 00:16:04.268
&gt;&gt; To get

00:16:04.268 --> 00:16:05.376
enough sunlight.

00:16:05.376 --> 00:16:05.775
&gt;&gt; Mm hmm.

00:16:05.775 --> 00:16:09.210
&gt;&gt; so that they can make enough vitamin D and that's even true for, for

00:16:09.210 --> 00:16:12.690
light skinned people too sometimes who, if you don't get out in the sun enough

00:16:14.950 --> 00:16:17.720
you know I believe even on ships when people crossed

00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:20.220
the Atlantic in the 15, 1600s, that, that was the

00:16:20.220 --> 00:16:22.650
thing right. They stayed if, if you didn't get enough

00:16:22.650 --> 00:16:25.860
sunlight, they call it scurvy, right? It's a vitamin D deficiency.

00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:26.250
&gt;&gt; Right.

00:16:26.250 --> 00:16:29.250
&gt;&gt; And really, the solution is just get out in the sun more.

00:16:29.250 --> 00:16:31.202
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:16:31.202 --> 00:16:34.690
&gt;&gt; What are there any other, is there

00:16:34.690 --> 00:16:36.810
any other positive or negative aspect, do you think,

00:16:36.810 --> 00:16:37.890
sorry, I should say this. Do you think

00:16:37.890 --> 00:16:40.180
other people look at skin color or skin pigmentation

00:16:40.180 --> 00:16:42.480
as a positive or negative trait? Maybe not so much

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:46.250
from the biological side, but from even a social perspective?

00:16:46.250 --> 00:16:51.340
&gt;&gt; Yeah, definitely. There are people who, who, there are people who

00:16:51.340 --> 00:16:56.960
think that their skin pigmentation is a positive thing.

00:16:56.960 --> 00:16:57.070
&gt;&gt; Mm hm.

00:16:57.070 --> 00:17:01.230
&gt;&gt; Or a negative thing. Whereas, if you're ostracised, or you're discriminated

00:17:01.230 --> 00:17:05.400
against, for the color of your skin, then you might to start

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:07.079
to think that it's a negative thing.

00:17:07.079 --> 00:17:07.540
&gt;&gt; Mm hm.

00:17:07.540 --> 00:17:09.510
&gt;&gt; Where is if it's helping you in

00:17:09.510 --> 00:17:11.859
life in general, then you'll think it's a positive

00:17:11.859 --> 00:17:15.700
thing. So depending on whether you know if I'm

00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:19.440
making it in life, so to speak because of

00:17:19.440 --> 00:17:20.609
the color of my skin, then I'm going to

00:17:20.609 --> 00:17:24.359
be very happy with my skin pigmentation. Versus if,

00:17:24.359 --> 00:17:27.180
it's the thing that's causing other people to react

00:17:27.180 --> 00:17:30.460
negatively towards me and that's a social thing. Then

00:17:30.460 --> 00:17:32.840
I'm going to start to hate the color

00:17:32.840 --> 00:17:35.770
of my skin, which is terrible because it's, it's

00:17:35.770 --> 00:17:40.030
a genetic trait that has nothing to do with who I am on the inner inside. So.

00:17:40.030 --> 00:17:42.540
&gt;&gt; Yeah. I, I completely understand that.

00:17:42.540 --> 00:17:43.040
&gt;&gt; Right.
&gt;&gt;

00:17:49.590 --> 00:17:54.140
So as you mentioned, the darkly pigmented people are way less likely to get

00:17:54.140 --> 00:17:55.280
skin cancer, I think the number is,

00:17:55.280 --> 00:17:57.540
like, they're, If you have lighter skin, you're

00:17:57.540 --> 00:18:02.380
500 times more likely to get skin cancer. Do you know anyone from Kenya who

00:18:02.380 --> 00:18:04.350
had skin cancer at all? Just trying

00:18:04.350 --> 00:18:07.070
to see if, reality bears out those statistics.

00:18:07.070 --> 00:18:09.730
&gt;&gt; I don't, I don't personally know anyone.

00:18:09.730 --> 00:18:12.400
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm. Is that ever a concern? Did, did

00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:14.770
they, I don't know if they have like, you know,

00:18:14.770 --> 00:18:15.920
in the United States, you know we have

00:18:15.920 --> 00:18:17.900
these people who are like, oh, put sunscreen on

00:18:17.900 --> 00:18:19.530
go outside put sunscreen on make sure you

00:18:19.530 --> 00:18:21.900
put sunscreen on. Do people say that in Kenya?

00:18:21.900 --> 00:18:27.215
&gt;&gt; No. I don't hear that too much. sunscreen is also expensive.

00:18:27.215 --> 00:18:28.110
[LAUGH]

00:18:28.110 --> 00:18:28.730
So.

00:18:28.730 --> 00:18:29.970
&gt;&gt; True.

00:18:29.970 --> 00:18:32.500
&gt;&gt; I think if it was. I think if people, there were

00:18:32.500 --> 00:18:36.190
more cases of skin cancer, the cost would not be an issue.

00:18:36.190 --> 00:18:36.941
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:18:36.941 --> 00:18:42.520
&gt;&gt; But, people just think to themselves, I my grandmother lived without

00:18:42.520 --> 00:18:46.270
it, my mother lived without it, I'll be fine without it probably.

00:18:46.270 --> 00:18:51.360
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm. In Kenya, is sickle cell anemia a common trait?

00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:53.210
&gt;&gt; I

00:18:53.210 --> 00:18:55.400
don't know how common it is, but I do

00:18:55.400 --> 00:18:57.680
know of people who've had it, or who have it.

00:18:57.680 --> 00:19:01.220
&gt;&gt; Yeah, and what are the symptoms of sickle cell anemia, or what

00:19:01.220 --> 00:19:04.040
was it like for those people that you know of who, who've had it?

00:19:04.040 --> 00:19:05.960
&gt;&gt; It was, something I didn't know

00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:08.610
was happening until they told me themselves.

00:19:08.610 --> 00:19:08.950
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:19:08.950 --> 00:19:11.460
&gt;&gt; with one person I always thought to myself that she looked a

00:19:11.460 --> 00:19:14.640
little sickly sometimes but I just thought that maybe she had a cold.

00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:15.481
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:19:15.481 --> 00:19:18.440
&gt;&gt; But, turns out that she had, or has

00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:19.005
sickle cell anemia.

00:19:19.005 --> 00:19:22.330
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm, is it, is it a big

00:19:22.330 --> 00:19:24.570
deal? I mean, does it seriously affect their lives?

00:19:24.570 --> 00:19:29.820
&gt;&gt; I'm not sure. I'm not sure if it does. I would imagine it does,

00:19:29.820 --> 00:19:33.130
but she's very private with it, and so I don't know how much it affected her.

00:19:34.370 --> 00:19:39.320
All in all, she seemed to function normally. You know, she would show up to

00:19:39.320 --> 00:19:42.000
class, and go through everything that we would

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:43.510
go through and then I'd think to myself,

00:19:43.510 --> 00:19:44.340
oh, she's sick again?

00:19:44.340 --> 00:19:47.930
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm. Is the new one. no one in your

00:19:47.930 --> 00:19:50.200
family, though, has ever been affected by sickle cell anemia?

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:50.300
&gt;&gt; No.

00:19:50.300 --> 00:19:51.260
&gt;&gt; That you know of.

00:19:51.260 --> 00:19:52.470
&gt;&gt; No, not in family.

00:19:52.470 --> 00:19:54.840
&gt;&gt; Do you know if you're a carrier for sickle cell anemia?

00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:56.420
&gt;&gt; I do know that, and I'm not.

00:19:56.420 --> 00:20:02.960
&gt;&gt; That's great. does that factor into any people's decisions

00:20:02.960 --> 00:20:07.700
about, you know, children? Do people worry about that having sickle cell anemia?

00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:08.570
&gt;&gt; I

00:20:08.570 --> 00:20:12.930
would imagine that in a family where it was common where it

00:20:12.930 --> 00:20:16.180
had been running through the family that they might consider it. But I've

00:20:16.180 --> 00:20:21.890
never heard of people getting that test because with some people they know

00:20:21.890 --> 00:20:25.020
it's not. It's more common in some tribes than it is in others.

00:20:25.020 --> 00:20:25.430
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:20:25.430 --> 00:20:27.270
&gt;&gt; And so I think in a tribe like mine where it

00:20:27.270 --> 00:20:34.430
rarely happens, I don't see why, I don't think they'd factor in sickle-cell

00:20:34.430 --> 00:20:39.720
anemia or whether they were carriers or not into who they would marry.

00:20:39.720 --> 00:20:44.540
&gt;&gt; Do you know of, the treatment for sickle cell anemia,

00:20:44.540 --> 00:20:47.510
I mean, for people who have it in Kenya, is it generally

00:20:47.510 --> 00:20:50.620
accessible, I mean is it, do people know about it, is

00:20:50.620 --> 00:20:54.620
it something that's able to be treated in general for most people?

00:20:54.620 --> 00:21:00.040
&gt;&gt; So, in a country like Kenya with a rural population that may be

00:21:00.040 --> 00:21:01.230
less literate.

00:21:01.230 --> 00:21:02.251
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:21:02.251 --> 00:21:04.500
&gt;&gt; They would be less likely to know about treatment

00:21:04.500 --> 00:21:09.660
options than a population that was more urban or more literate.

00:21:09.660 --> 00:21:10.261
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:21:10.261 --> 00:21:12.340
&gt;&gt; Not necessarily the same thing, but more literate.

00:21:12.340 --> 00:21:12.970
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm.

00:21:12.970 --> 00:21:14.890
&gt;&gt; They would know more and would have access

00:21:14.890 --> 00:21:17.345
to treatment, so it depends on the region as well.

00:21:17.345 --> 00:21:21.916
&gt;&gt; Mm-hm. Kagure, why is sickle-cell anemia en,

00:21:21.916 --> 00:21:24.780
endemic to regions like Kenya in, in Africa.

00:21:24.780 --> 00:21:25.392
&gt;&gt; I think

00:21:25.392 --> 00:21:30.594
it's something that developed in order to I think it's

00:21:30.594 --> 00:21:35.796
something that developed as your, your body's response,

00:21:35.796 --> 00:21:40.940
or our body's response to a fight or stave off for malaria.

00:21:40.940 --> 00:21:44.020
&gt;&gt; Say say just say to

00:21:46.160 --> 00:21:50.650
resistant to malaria. It exists. Well it exists. It's higher

00:21:50.650 --> 00:21:53.580
on the region because it also provides some resistance to malaria.

00:21:53.580 --> 00:21:57.130
&gt;&gt; Okay. So it's higher in the region

00:21:57.130 --> 00:22:01.020
because it provides resistance, some resistance to malaria.

00:22:01.020 --> 00:22:05.310
&gt;&gt; So, malaria is a common, sickness.

00:22:05.310 --> 00:22:06.360
&gt;&gt; Yes, definitely.

00:22:06.360 --> 00:22:07.080
&gt;&gt; Definitely.

00:22:07.080 --> 00:22:10.680
&gt;&gt; I've had malaria, everyone else in my family has had malaria too, so.

00:22:10.680 --> 00:22:11.270
&gt;&gt; Really?

00:22:11.270 --> 00:22:12.940
What's it like to have malaria?

00:22:12.940 --> 00:22:20.190
&gt;&gt; you, malaria is like the flu. I've never had the flu, but from what people

00:22:20.190 --> 00:22:22.550
describe the flu as, you get dizzy, you

00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:26.540
get nauseous, you get achy joints. when I

00:22:26.540 --> 00:22:29.070
had malaria, I remember being very dizzy, dizzy

00:22:29.070 --> 00:22:31.300
enough that the floor seemed very far away

00:22:31.300 --> 00:22:36.280
and like it was teetering. And you're just kind of out of it, you get a

00:22:36.280 --> 00:22:37.630
fever, the usual.

00:22:37.630 --> 00:22:39.650
&gt;&gt; And how does the, I mean how does

00:22:39.650 --> 00:22:44.200
malaria spread. We'll wrap up by our conversation of skin

00:22:44.200 --> 00:22:46.930
pigmentation, and what I want to do is just give

00:22:46.930 --> 00:22:50.670
you an opportunity to, to tell us anything you might

00:22:50.670 --> 00:22:53.560
want to share, you know a lot of people have,

00:22:53.560 --> 00:22:56.080
a lot of people think differently about skin color. Some

00:22:56.080 --> 00:22:57.890
people it's a big deal, other people it's not a

00:22:57.890 --> 00:23:02.010
big deal. If you could give advice or just say

00:23:02.010 --> 00:23:06.630
anything speaking to that idea in people about whether or not skin color's a

00:23:06.630 --> 00:23:10.610
big deal or not. what would you say or what advice would you give?

00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:15.820
&gt;&gt; I think the advice I'd give is that it

00:23:15.820 --> 00:23:18.890
shouldn't matter. It would be naive of me to say

00:23:18.890 --> 00:23:22.520
that you should ignore it because others are not ignoring

00:23:22.520 --> 00:23:27.120
it, and so you should be aware of how others will

00:23:27.120 --> 00:23:29.780
treat you but all in all it doesn't,

00:23:29.780 --> 00:23:31.920
it shouldn't change who, it doesn't change who you

00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:34.960
are on the inside, it's. A genetic trait that

00:23:34.960 --> 00:23:38.560
simply dictates what the color of your skin, and

00:23:38.560 --> 00:23:43.610
so, after that, it may have it's biological advantages

00:23:43.610 --> 00:23:46.810
or disadvantages. But in the end, it doesn't, it

00:23:46.810 --> 00:23:49.970
doesn't, your skin color is not your ethnicity, it

00:23:49.970 --> 00:23:53.010
isn't your race. Race is a social construct and

00:23:53.010 --> 00:23:57.650
so, it doesn't change who you are on the inside. It really

00:23:57.650 --> 00:24:02.340
shouldn't matter and it would be great to say that it doesn't matter,

00:24:02.340 --> 00:24:06.170
but to some it does. My advice would be to be you, be

00:24:06.170 --> 00:24:11.150
who you are. I mean, nobody, nobody cares to be who you are.

